## PHASE 3 — CORE SETUP FILES

Build these files first — they are the foundation everything else depends on:

1. `src/types/author.ts` — Author interface with all fields needed for schema
2. `src/data/authors.ts` — Ri and Jyoti with all real data, social URLs, knowsAbout, etc. Include helper functions `getAuthorBySlug()` and `getAuthorByName()`
3. `src/lib/generateSchemas.ts` — Full schema library including:
   - `generateJyotiSchema()` — Person schema for Jyoti
   - `generateRiSchema()` — Person schema for Ri
   - `resolveAuthorSchema(authorName)` — resolves post.author string to correct Person schema
   - `generateOrganizationSchema()` — clean org schema
   - `generateWebsiteSchema()` — website schema with SearchAction
   - `generateBlogSchema()` — blog entity schema
   - `generateArticleSchema(post)` — BlogPosting schema
   - `generateFAQSchema(items)` — FAQPage schema
   - `generateBreadcrumbSchema(items)` — BreadcrumbList schema
   - `generateHowToSchema()` — HowTo schema for tutorial posts
   - `generateAboutPageSchema()` — AboutPage schema
   - `generateContactPageSchema(email)` — ContactPage schema
   - All schemas must be consistent: same brand name, same logo path, same social handles
4. `src/lib/seo.ts` — Central metadata helper with `generatePageMetadata(input)` function that all pages will call. Must include all best-practice fields: canonical, openGraph with article fields, twitter, robots, authors
5. `src/app/layout.tsx` — Root layout with:
   - Separate `viewport` export (Next.js 15 requirement — not inside metadata)
   - Both Person schemas (Jyoti + Ri) in structured data
   - Organization + Website schemas
   - Consistent brand name, correct logo path, correct social handles
6. `public/site.webmanifest` — Fixed with real brand name, correct colors, correct icon paths

