## PHASE 4 — METADATA AUDIT SCRIPT

After core files are done, build a script the user runs locally:

```
node scripts/audit-metadata.js
```

It should:
- Scan every `page.tsx` and `layout.tsx` in `src/app/`
- Scan every `.md` and `.mdx` file in `src/content/`
- Extract: title, description, canonical, openGraph, author, datePublished, dateModified, image
- Flag issues: missing fields, titles too short/long, descriptions too short/long, missing canonical, missing OG image, missing author
- Output a structured report to `metadata-audit-report.json` AND a human-readable `metadata-audit-report.txt`
- The txt report should group issues by severity: CRITICAL, WARNING, INFO

