## PHASE 5 — PAGE-BY-PAGE METADATA OPTIMIZATION

After the audit report is generated and reviewed:

- User shares the report
- You go page by page optimizing titles and descriptions for CTR
- Every title must: be under 60 chars, include the primary keyword, have a hook that makes someone want to click
- Every description must: be under 155 chars, expand on the title, include a benefit or curiosity gap, end with an implicit or explicit CTA
- Wire `generatePageMetadata()` into every page that isn't using it yet
- For blog `page.tsx` — map `post.author` to the correct Person schema automatically

